Riot is an unlawful assembly in a particular state of activity. To constitute the offence
of rioting it must be proved:
(1)that the accused, being ﬁve or more in number, formed an unlawful assembly;
(2)that they were animated by a common unlawful object;
(3)that force or violence was used by the unlawful assembly or any member of it;
